\[

The basis for the null space is given by the vectors: 

\[
\begin{pmatrix} -3.5 \\ 0 \\ -0.2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}
\] 

and 

\[
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}, 
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}. 
\] 

So one basis vector can be: 
\[
\begin{pmatrix} -3.5 \\ 0 \\ -0.2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}
\]
and any linear combination of: 
\[
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} 
\text{ and } 
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}. 
\] 

Thus, basis vectors are: 
\[
\begin{pmatrix} -3.5 \\ 0 \\ -0.2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}, 
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}, 
\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}. 
\]
